She grew up in a house where dreams were folded away neatly, hidden between books she wasn’t allowed to read.
Where asking for a night out felt like asking for the world.
Where what she wore, where she went, what she said — was measured, controlled, decided.
She was meant to live a life stitched in small, safe corners.
Marry young, settle down, shrink herself into the life she was handed.

But somewhere deep inside, a fire refused to go out.
A whisper too loud to ignore.
A stubborn little voice that said — maybe there’s more.

Today, she stands on beaches she once only saw in magazines.
She laughs under open skies with friends she once wasn’t allowed to meet.
She wears what she loves, walks into events she once only watched from a screen.
She’s invited to Lakme Fashion Week.
She works jobs she once believed belonged to ‘other’ people.
She’s no longer waiting for permission.
She’s building a life that once felt too big to even dream about.

And maybe… she still doesn’t realize just how far she’s come.
Sometimes, I just want to tell her — slow down, breathe.
You made it. And you’re still making it.

Ever seen that colorful tape athletes wear? 🏃‍♂️
It’s more than just a fashion statement —
It’s called therapeutic taping — a rehab game-changer! ⚡

OTs don’t just help you move — we help you stick the landing! 🎯✨

🎀 Welcome to the world of therapeutic taping:
Not just colorful strips, but functional tools for:
✔️ Supporting developing muscles 💪👶
✔️ Encouraging better posture 🧍‍♀️➡️🧍‍♂️
✔️ Reducing sensory overload 🤯➡️😌
✔️ Assisting joint alignment 🦴📐
✔️ Promoting independence in movement 🚶‍♀️🆓

From floppy tone to hypermobile joints — we tape with purpose!
Because when you’re an OT, even a roll of tape becomes a superpower! 🦸‍♀️🎗️
